  "texts": [
    "Specifically, (Albanese and Feuerstein 2021) introduced a community pooling-based Twitter topic modeling method that cleverly incorporates the Louvain community detection algorithm (Blondel et al. 2008).",
    "It efficiently aggregates tweets from the same community on the user interaction graph by maximizing the modularity through a greedy optimization strategy.",
    "This innovation not only increases the amount of information in a single document but also reduces the total number of processed documents, thus achieving superior performance over traditional methods on two heterogeneous Twitter datasets.",
    "To address the complexity of fake news detection, (Chen et al. 2022) proposed an innovative contextual attention pooling function.",
    "This pooling function applies the self-attention mechanism to dynamically assign weights to different posts and integrates the multi-level pooling results through jump connections across network layers, which provides the model with multi-scale observation perspectives and stronger graph structure adaptability."
  ],
